By Tomisin Erogbogbo Lagos – A 32-year-old salesperson, Abolade Adebayo, who allegedly stole his employer’s N1.5 million was on Thursday brought before a Tinubu Magistrates’ Court. Abolade whose address was not provided, is facing a charge of theft and he pleaded innocence of the offence. The Prosecutor, Insp. Ajaga Agboko, told the court that the defendant committed the offence on May 4 at 3:20 p.m., at 49/51 Martins St., off Tom Jones, Lagos Island. He alleged that the defendant, who was a salesperson at a clothing store where lace materials were sold, stole N1.5 million belonging to his employer, Mrs Kofoworola Adebutu. Agboko also alleged that Adebayo stole the N1.5 million sales proceeds which Adebutu left in the drawer to be taken to the bank. “The defendant who was acting suspicious in his attempt to abscond, was later caught,’’ he alleged. The offence contravenes Section 287 (7) of the Criminal Law of Lagos State, 2015; which attracts seven years imprisonment for theft. The Magistrate, Mr T. A. Anjorin-Ajose, granted the defendant N200,000 bail with two sureties in like sum. He said that one of the sureties must be a relative of the defendant and the other a civil servant. Further hearing on the case has been fixed for July 22.